This paper deals with visual understanding and relationship detection, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of embeddings and semantic affinity, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a visual module and a semantic module, which are common in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with a large dataset and performance evaluation, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM).
